com.assylias.jbloomberg

Class ReferenceRequestBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.assylias.jbloomberg.ReferenceRequestBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RequestBuilder<ReferenceData>

    public final class ReferenceRequestBuilder
extends Object
    This class enables to build a ReferenceData request while ensuring argument safety. Typically, instead of passing strings arguments (and typos) as with the standard Bloomberg API, the possible options used to override the behaviour of the query have been wrapped in enums or relevant primitive types.

    All methods, including the constructors, throw NullPointerException when null arguments are passed in.

    Once the request has been built, the ReferenceRequestBuilder can be submitted to a BloombergSession.

    This class is not thread safe.

      • ReferenceRequestBuilder

        public ReferenceRequestBuilder(Collection<String> tickers,
                               Collection<String> fields)
        Creates a ReferenceRequestBuilder. The fields parameters can be overriden with the provided methods.

        Parameters:
        tickers - a collection of tickers for which data needs to be retrieved - tickers must be valid Bloomberg symbols (for example: IBM US Equity)
        fields - a collection of Bloomberg fields to retrieve for each ticker

        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if any of the parameters is null or if the collections contain null items
        IllegalArgumentException - if any of the collections is empty or contains empty strings
